BIKINI (HDR)

Hostage Rescue Map for Counter-Strike: Source

CS:S initial map creator (LDR version 2005): 3D-Mike
CS:S final map editor (HDR version 2018): Niko
Navigation Mesh editor: Meurglis3

Essential renovation of the legendary Hostage Rescue map for CS:S cs_bikini by 3D-Mike (released February 2005).

General changes (improvements) in comparison with the original initial release:
   - Map compiled with HDR (instead the LDR-compiled original);
   - Considerably increased the performance (an average gain ~ 50 fps);
   - Corrected the critical error significantly influencing a strategy of gameplay (Hostage Rescue Zone didn't extend to an area of underground pass with ladder that didn't allow to rescue the hostages through a tunnel's path);
   - Added a significant amount of decorative content (for a bigger variety and revival of the environment);
   - Added and/or simplified for usage several minor paths (which significantly influencing to the intensity and fascination of a gameplay).

Story:
   After arrest of the previous owner the Bikini Hangout mansion at the Paradise Bay has been sold at auction. The new owner of the estate has decided that the house is in need of repair. Therefore he has employed construction crew from among illegal immigrants. And that was his serious mistake... 'cause the terrorists who have pretended the workers have captured the employee of the estate as the hostages. And now FBI is forced to storm this hornet's nest!

P.S. ~ Dont forget to bring yer swimming trunks! :-)

Well its 12:55 am, I'm red-eyed and extremely tired after working all day on this damned map, and I've got school at 6:00 am tomorrow, but I can proudly say, it's ready for beta-release.

It's been 2 days of work, which wouldn't seem like a lot but I literally sat on the computer all weekend (had the flu) and clicked, clicked, typed and clicked. But you don't care do you, you want to hear about the map:

It's 12:55 A.M. and you get the call from the SWAT chief, there's a hostage situation at the city bank. Right before closing, 10 heavily armed men came in, barricaded the doors, and took 2 of the employees that knew the vault security number. You hop in your car and head down to meet with your 9 well-armed companions in the back, where the robbers have attempted to tunnel out of the basement. Your objective: Kill the robbers and rescue the hostages. You've got 3 options for entry:

Hop into the tunnel with no return and hope to god you can take them;

Enter through the back entrance into the vault;

or bust through the skylight light an action star and take siege of the place.

Now that you've heard the fancy description here's some general information:

It was made by me, obviously, entirely, so please check out my profile:
http://www.fpsbanana.com/members/608513

My reason for creating it was a desire to add another submission to my studio:
http://www.fpsbanana.com/studios/21716

and the map WOULD NOT be possible without the perfect skybox from Karatekaefer:

//His profile: http://www.fpsbanana.com/members/138831

//The texture itself, Mpa100: http://www.fpsbanana.com/textures/1034

So please enjoy the map, and yea, it may seem a bit drab, but it's been tested on a 20 slot server and it was a lot of fun with max players!

STORY:

Its 2009, just outside Chicago, Nothern USA. After a botched bankjob terrorist from a wide variety of cells have taken hostages in a little uptown bank. Counter-Terrorists Units from across the world have been called into action putting forward their best or best from each special forces teams.

Lethal force has been confimed...


Special Notes:

cs_bankjob will be heavily TACTICAL based. CTs will HAVE to work as a team in order to not get prawned. 
Some special features of cs_bankjob will be:

-	CCTV, around the outside of building cameras have been operational, terrorists have the ability to see out 	onto particular areas of the building. CTs use smoke, tread carefully, your being watched.

-	Breaching Charges, special areas of the building have been rigged, some walls and some doors. CTs will 			have the ability to blast through the walls and storm in at the push of a button.

-	Alpha Team and Bravo Team, CTs are split into 2 offensive teams; Alpha team begin the round at the front 		of the building while Bravo Team infiltrate from the side alley of the building


Extract all Files into your cstrike/maps folder

Inspired by the California Bank shoot out back in the 1990s.
This farily balanced out with equal camp areas and choke points it makes for a fun tactical game.

Remake of cs_bank http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/116919

Mission Briefing
Thieves (Terrorists) have taken over G.N.B. (A reference to How I met Your Mother, Goliath National Bank) and have taken hostages. Negotiations have been a failure. We (Counter Terrorist) have secured the perimeter, and no one can escape without us noticing. Your objective is to Rescue the hostages by any means necessary. Our satellite reveals that the robbers are all spread out in corridors as general surveillance, a back alley providing guard from the Back doors, others are located inside the vault taking the money and a few are holding the hostages, so expect heavy fire as soon as you get there.
-Good Luck Gentlemen

Game play
It’s a Bank situation, but it’s a slightly different game play than usual CS games. In here Action is instant. All CT start at the entrance with an option to buy weapons, However the Terrorist team are all spread out over bank (Some start in corridors as general surveillance, a back alley providing guard from the Back doors, others are located inside the vault taking the money and a few are holding the hostages). The hostages are just a few feet away, yet its not as simple as rushing in as that ends up in death, so CT have to fight and try to flank using other entrances to the bank.

The inspiration came from having watching a few bank robberies movies, and the fact that I have never played a bank map in here, so it looked like an interesting concept to make. I am very happy with the results.

Features
-Different spawning points for Terrorist.
-Hostages are relatively close to rescue zone, yet it is a challenge to rescue them quickly
-A Detailed World
-Physics objects get destroyed and fly around
-Optimized map, with an average of 170 fps, with a decent computer

--Added a possible soultion for radar not showing up properly

Capacity
32 vs. 32
